From a6f442f95795333f929aa7dce98f32ab5dbba8ed Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@local>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 19:35:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 6/8] umd: include limits for numeric_limits use

The UMD Type.h helper uses std::numeric_limits in saturate(), but the header
does not include <limits>. Older toolchains may have exposed numeric_limits
indirectly through another C++ header, but GCC 12/libstdc++ does not guarantee
that and fails to build the runtime.

Include <limits> where std::numeric_limits is used. This is a local include
fix and does not change the UMD ABI or runtime behavior.

Tested: ARM64 Buildroot GCC 12.4.0 runtime compile.
Signed-off-by: Codex <codex@local>
---
 umd/core/src/common/include/priv/Type.h | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/umd/core/src/common/include/priv/Type.h b/umd/core/src/common/include/priv/Type.h
index 4c186e5..fba3ea1 100644
--- a/umd/core/src/common/include/priv/Type.h
+++ b/umd/core/src/common/include/priv/Type.h
@@ -33,6 +33,7 @@
 #include <sstream>
 #include <map>
 #include <algorithm>
+#include <limits>
 #include <exception>
 
 #include "nvdla/IType.h"
